        "content": "<p>Hi! I am stumbling upon a seemingly basic problem, where if (a : ℤ) ∈ (A : Set ℤ), then I want to use that a : A. I assume this requires some sort of casting. What syntax should I use? Is another approach more suitable to solve this issue?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Basic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">zero_in_set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">irreducible</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">irreducible</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 461025797,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Lehéricy",
        "timestamp": 1723483503
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i'd advise you to rather state it like <code>∀ k ∈ K, ∃ j ∈ K, P j k</code> to entirely circumvent this.</p>",
        "id": 461026229,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723483638
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if that doesn't work: you can get the <em>corresponding</em> element (not the same one, as terms have only one type) by using anonymous constructors: <code>⟨k,hk⟩</code> where <code>k : ℤ</code> and <code>hk : k ∈ K</code></p>",
        "id": 461026635,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723483768
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for going the other way, if <code>j : K</code>, then <code>j.property : j.val ∈ K</code></p>",
        "id": 461027042,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723483857
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but like i said, this can be probably avoided if you use the notation i mentioned first.</p>",
        "id": 461027162,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723483880
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"684366\">Edward van de Meent</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Casting.20elements/near/461026229\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>i'd advise you to rather state it like <code>∀ k ∈ K, ∃ j ∈ K, P j k</code> to entirely circumvent this.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This works fine, thank you!</p>",
